<TITLE> BSF agree to take action over border death </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Satkhira, Apr 3(bdnews24.com)--- The Bangladesh Defence Rifles (BDR) and Border Security Force (BSF) both agreed to maintain peace and stability along the border during a commander level flag meeting on Saturday. The flag meeting took place at about 1 pm at Baladghat near the Satkhira border in Bangladesh territory. following a strong protest from the BDR after a Bangladeshi cow trader was shot dead by the BSF. BDR had also alleged that the BSF men were digging a canal along Kaliani border defying the border agreement. Commander Lt. Col Iqbal Azim led the 41 Rifles Battalion delegation while Commandant Ananda Singh led the group from the BSF 94 Battalion.. During the one hour meeting, the BSF regretted the death on Friday and assured the BDR that it would take action against the culprits. The BSF have also agreed to stop digging soil within 150 yards of the Kaliani border. bd
